#: ../../O/overflow-bit.rst:5
msgid "overflow bit"
msgstr "overflow bit"

#: ../../O/overflow-bit.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../O/overflow-bit.rst:10
msgid ""
"[techspeak] A :ref:`flag` on some processors indicating an attempt to "
"calculate a result too large for a register to hold."
msgstr ""
"[techspeak]一部のプロセッサにある\\ :ref:`flag`\\ で、レジスタに収まらないほど大きな結果を計算しようとしたことを示すもの。"

#: ../../O/overflow-bit.rst:13
msgid ""
"More generally, an indication of any kind of capacity overload condition. "
"\"Well, the Ada description was :ref:`baroque` all right, but I could hack "
"it OK until they got to the exception handling ... that set my overflow "
"bit.\""
msgstr ""
"より一般的には、あらゆる種類の容量過負荷状態を示すもの。「まあ、Adaの記述はたしかに\\ :ref:`baroque`\\ "
"だったが、例外処理に入るまではなんとかhackできた……あれで俺のoverflow bitが立った」"

#: ../../O/overflow-bit.rst:17
msgid ""
"The hypothetical bit that will be set if a hacker doesn't get to make a trip"
" to the Room of Porcelain Fixtures: \"I'd better process an internal "
"interrupt before the overflow bit gets set.\""
msgstr ""
"ハッカーがPorcelain Fixturesの部屋(訳注:トイレ)へ行く機会を得られないと立つであろう仮想のビット。「overflow "
"bitが立つ前に内部割り込みを処理したほうがよさそうだ」"

#: ../../O/overflow-bit.rst:23
msgid "Crunchly and the  :ref:`overflow-bit`\\."
msgstr "Crunchlyと\\ :ref:`overflow-bit`\\ 。"

#: ../../O/overflow-bit.rst:25
msgid ""
"(The next cartoon in the Crunchly saga is         "
":ref:`73-07-29<crunchly73-07-29>`\\.  The previous one is         "
":ref:`73-06-04<crunchly73-06-04>`\\.)"
msgstr ""
"(Crunchlyサーガの次の漫画は\\ :ref:`73-07-29<crunchly73-07-29>`\\ 。前のものは\\ "
":ref:`73-06-04<crunchly73-06-04>`\\ 。)"
